This paper focuses on natural language processing (NLP) and specifically on unsupervised lemmatization, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The proposed method involves clustering word forms based on their embeddings, which is a common technique in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of cosine similarity and Jaro-Winkler edit distance also suggests a potential connection to information retrieval (cs.IR) and neural networks (cs.NE).
